 PHP built-in server — development use:

		1.cd /path/to/your/project
		2.sudo php -S 127.0.0.1:8080
					or
		   php -S 127.0.0.1:8080		
Notes
	sudo mukkiyam illa for port 8080. (Port <1024-na sudo venum.)

	Stop panna: Ctrl + C in terminal.

	If you want other devices in same LAN to access: php -S 0.0.0.0:8080 (security risk — only if you trust the network).

	To serve a specific directory: php -S 127.0.0.1:8080 -t public

	Router script (for frameworks): php -S 127.0.0.1:8080 router.php	
 
 Apache Server:
 	sudo apt update
	sudo apt install apache2
  start/enable/status:
  	sudo systemctl start apache2
	sudo systemctl enable apache2     # boot-kku auto start
	sudo systemctl status apache2     # service status check


Check logs if fail. Try curl:
	curl -I http://127.0.0.1/hello.html

